			<abstract>
<div xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><p>The diffusion properties of Li in an andesitic and pitchstone melt have been determined over the temperature range 1300-1400°C.</p><p>The diffusion data have been fitted to an Arrhenius relationship between log D o and I/T, and give relatively small activation energies of diffusion: 21.4 _+ 5.8 kcal mol-1 in the andesite and 20.1 +_ 2.8 kcal mol-l in the pitchstone.</p><p>Li +, unlike several other cations, shows similar diffusivities in these melt compositions to that in a basaltic melt. Despite the similar ionic radius of Li + to that of Co 2+, the diffusion properties of the two ions are very different from each other.</p></div>
			</abstract>
		</profileDesc>
